<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669871>
    dc:description "FIGURE 71. Scyliorhinus stellaris; lateral view. A, NHMUK 1976.7.30.10–12, male, 448.9 mm TL (Banyuls, Pyrenees, France); B, ZMB 4429, male, 388.9 mm CT (Mediterranean Sea); C, ZMB 19943, female, 315.7 mm TL (Rovinj, Croatia); D, ZMH 100686, male, 305.1 mm TL (English Channel, 49°53’N, 0°27’E). Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669871/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669873>
    dc:description "FIGURE 72. Scyliorhinus stellaris. A, E, USNM 221693, female, 483 mm TL (Gulf of Trieste, Croatia, 45°30’N, 13°32’E); B, F, NHMUK 1976.7.30.10-12, male, 476 mm TL (Banyuls, Pyrenees, France); C, D, ZMH 100686, male, 305.1 mm TL (English Channel, 49°53’N, 0°27’E); A, B, ventral view of head; C, lateral view of head; D, dorsal view of head; E, detail of pelvic fins in females; F, detail of pelvic fins and claspers. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669873/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669875>
    dc:description "FIGURE 73. Teeth of Scyliorhinus stellaris; labial view, NHMUK 1971.7.21.4, female, 501.3 mm TL (Sezimbra Bay, Portugal). a, anterior tooth; c, commissural; l, lateral; ps, parassymphysial. Scale bar = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669875/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669877>
    dc:description "FIGURE 74. Dermal denticles of Scyliorhinus stellaris, NHMUK 1971.7.21.4, female, 501.3 mm TL (Sezimbra Bay, Portugal). A, region above pectoral fin base; B, region below first dorsal fin origin; C, region below second dorsal fin insertion. Scale bar = 250 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669877/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669879>
    dc:description "FIGURE 75. Clasper of Scyliorhinus stellaris; dorsal view, NHMUK 1976.7.30.10, 476 mm TL (Banyuls, Pyrenees, France). A, external morphology; B, skeleton. crh, cover rhipidion; end, endstyle; erh, exorhipidion; hp, hipopyle; rd, dorsal marginal cartilage; rh, rhipidion; rv, ventral marginal cartilage; td, dorsal terminal cartilage; td2, dorsal terminal 2 cartilage; tdc, terminal dermal cover; tv, ventral terminal cartilage; tv2, ventral terminal 2 cartilage. Scale bar = 20 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2669879/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2669881>
    dc:description "FIGURE 76. Map showing the geographic distribution of Scyliorhinus stellaris based on material examined in this study. Black star indicates the neotype locality." ;
